# ⚡ European Electricity Load Forecasting

Machine Learning project for short-term electricity demand forecasting across European countries using weather data, time-series features, and XGBoost regression models.

The project combines electricity load data with weather information to predict the next 24 hours of electricity demand and provides an interactive Streamlit dashboard for model visualization and comparison.

---

# 📌 Project Overview

Electricity demand forecasting is a critical task for modern energy systems, helping grid operators optimize production, balance supply and demand, and improve renewable energy integration.

This project implements an end-to-end forecasting pipeline:

1. Data collection
2. Data preprocessing
3. Weather integration
4. Feature engineering
5. Machine learning training
6. Model evaluation
7. 24-hour recursive forecasting
8. Interactive dashboard deployment


---

# 🌍 Supported Countries

The system currently supports four European countries:

- 🇩🇪 Germany
- 🇫🇷 France
- 🇪🇸 Spain
- 🇳🇱 Netherlands


Each country has its own trained XGBoost forecasting model.


