# 📊 Data Sources

## Electricity Load Data

Electricity demand data is based on ENTSO-E transparency datasets.

Used variables include:

- Actual electricity load
- Generation information
- Renewable energy indicators


## Weather Data

Weather information is collected from Open-Meteo historical weather API.

Features include:

- Temperature
- Wind speed
- Cloud cover
- Solar radiation


---

# ⚙️ Feature Engineering

The forecasting models use engineered time-series features:

## Calendar Features

- Hour
- Month
- Weekday
- Weekend indicator


## Lag Features

Historical electricity demand:

- Previous hour load
- Previous day load
- Previous week load


## Rolling Statistics

- 24-hour rolling mean
- 24-hour rolling standard deviation


## Cyclic Features

Time encoding using:

- Hour sine transformation
- Hour cosine transformation


These features allow the model to capture daily and weekly demand patterns.


---

# 🤖 Machine Learning Model

The project uses:

## XGBoost Regressor


Main parameters:


n_estimators = 500

learning_rate = 0.05

max_depth = 6

random_state = 42



The model is trained separately for each country.

Training strategy:

- 80% training data
- 20% testing data
- Time-series split without shuffling


---

# 📈 Model Performance


| Country | MAE (MW) | RMSE (MW) | MAPE |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| Germany | 355.81 | 488.25 | 0.66% |
| France | 338.74 | 701.34 | 0.65% |
| Spain | 174.31 | 267.52 | 0.64% |
| Netherlands | 100.08 | 150.95 | 0.81% |


Performance metrics:

- MAE: Mean Absolute Error
- RMSE: Root Mean Squared Error
- MAPE: Mean Absolute Percentage Error


---

# 🔮 Forecasting Approach

The application generates a 24-hour electricity demand forecast using recursive forecasting.

Process:


Historical Load

  ↓

Feature Generation

  ↓

XGBoost Prediction

  ↓

Prediction added to history

  ↓

Next hour forecast

  ↓

Repeat until 24 hours



---

# 🖥️ Streamlit Dashboard


The interactive dashboard provides:


## Forecast Dashboard

Features:

- Country selection
- Historical electricity demand visualization
- Current load KPI
- Average load KPI
- Peak demand KPI
- Model performance metrics
- 24-hour forecast generation
- Actual vs Forecast comparison


## Model Comparison

Allows comparison between European countries:

- MAE ranking
- RMSE comparison
- Performance table


